overview: The user initiated a comprehensive review of their sleep questionnaire
  application, providing a detailed specification. The agent performed an
  initial assessment, identifying several critical gaps in the implementation.
  Subsequently, the agent began implementing the identified high-priority
  features. This involved adding a 1-10 severity scale for tiredness, complete
  with a safety warning for high scores, which required updates across data
  types, validation, UI components, and both web and PDF report generation. The
  agent also successfully implemented detection logic for Comorbid Insomnia and
  Sleep Apnea (COMISA) and Insufficient Sleep Syndrome, integrating these new
  diagnoses and their respective recommendations into the user reports. The
  implementation process was systematic, with the agent tracking progress and
  performing lint checks to ensure code quality.
